# Cloudflare Zero Trust MITM certificate — optional.
#
# If your organisation uses Cloudflare Zero Trust with TLS inspection enabled,
# paste the root CA certificate here in PEM format.  The Dockerfile checks
# whether this file is non-empty; if so it installs it as a trusted CA inside
# the sandbox container so OpenCode's outbound HTTPS traffic to model providers
# can pass through the ZT gateway without certificate errors.
#
# If you are NOT using ZT inspection, leave this file empty (or delete its
# contents).  An empty file causes the Dockerfile to skip the cert-install
# step entirely.
#
# To obtain the certificate: Cloudflare Zero Trust dashboard →
# Settings → Network → TLS Inspection → Download certificate.
